# AsFix Security Rules

## Secrets
- Never commit `.env`, tokens, passwords, or `backend/data/data.json` with real customer data
- Use `.env.example` for documented vars only (`CORS_ORIGIN`, `NODE_ENV`, `PORT`)
- Shop phone/email live in `frontend/src/config/shop.js` — no API keys in frontend

## Backend API
- All admin/staff routes must use `requireAuth` + `requireRole`
- Public write endpoints (`/api/contact`, `/api/orders`, `/api/repairs/book`) need rate limits and input length caps
- Keep JSON body limit small (256kb); reject oversized payloads
- Production: set `CORS_ORIGIN` to exact domain(s); never use `cors()` wide open in prod
- Error responses: generic message only — no stack traces or internal paths to clients

## Auth
- Passwords hashed with scrypt (`backend/auth/crypto.js`) — never store plain text
- Sessions use random tokens; expire inactive sessions
- Login endpoint must stay rate-limited (brute-force protection)

## Input
- Trim and validate all user strings; enforce max lengths on contact/order/repair forms
- Reject unexpected types (arrays/objects where strings expected)
- No `eval`, no dynamic `require`, no unsanitized HTML injection in stored messages

## Frontend
- Auth token in localStorage is acceptable for this app; clear on 401/403 only
- Never log tokens or passwords to console in production builds
- Staff panels poll only when tab visible — use `startVisibilityPoll`

## Deploy checklist
- `NODE_ENV=production`
- HTTPS via Render/Vercel (free SSL)
- Reset default admin password after first deploy (`npm run reset-admin`)
- Review `DEPLOY.md` before going live
